<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1527,1914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,603,1527,1554]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Descripion and differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Deng, Xin &amp; Chen published a redescription in 2018, (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Deng, W. A. &amp; Xin, L. &amp; Wei, Q. &amp; Chen, Y. Z." pageId="5" pageNumber="350" pagination="421 - 430" refId="ref12274" refString="Deng, W. A., Xin, L., Wei, Q. &amp; Chen, Y. Z. (2018) Two new species of the genus Macromotettix Gunther, 1939 (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae, Metrodorinae) from China, with a key to the species of the genus. Zootaxa, 4370 (4), 421 - 430. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4370.4.7" type="journal article" year="2018">Deng, Xin &amp; Chen 2018</bibRefCitation>
). This genus is similar to 
<emphasis box="[583,711,1563,1589]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Bolivarittix</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gunther, K." box="[720,886,1563,1590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" pagination="1 - 335" refId="ref12512" refString="Gunther, K. (1939) Revision der Acrydiinae (Orthoptera), III. Sectio Amorphopi (Metrodorae Bol. 1887 auct.). Abhandlungen und Berichte der Museum fur Tierkunde und Volkerkunde zu Dresden, (A), 20, 1 - 335." type="journal article" year="1939">Günther, 1939</bibRefCitation>
, but differs from humeral apex ridge and lower margin of pronotum connected in the middle or behind middle of lower margin of pronotum (humeral apex ridge and lower margin of pronotum connected before middle of lower margin of pronotum in 
<emphasis box="[1167,1295,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Bolivarittix</emphasis>
Günther). It appears similar also to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng, Wei &amp; Jiang, 2005" authorityName="Zheng, Wei &amp; Jiang" authorityYear="2005" box="[404,925,1671,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettixoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[404,627,1671,1697]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Macromotettixoides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng, Z. M. &amp; Wei, Z. M. &amp; Jiang, G. F." box="[633,925,1671,1698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" pagination="366 - 367" refId="ref13894" refString="Zheng, Z. M., Wei, Z. M. &amp; Jiang, G. F. (2005) A new genus and a new species of Metrodoridae (Orthoptera) from China. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 30 (2), 366 - 367." type="journal article" year="2005">Zheng, Wei &amp; Jiang, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by posterior margin of each lateral lobe of pronotum with ventral sinus and tegminal (upper) sinus (posterior margin of each lateral lobe of pronotum only with ventral sinus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng, Wei &amp; Jiang" authorityYear="2005" box="[589,812,1743,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettixoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[589,812,1743,1769]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Macromotettixoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1527,1914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,559,1779,1806]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Composition and distribution.</emphasis>
Twenty-four species are previously assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Gunther. In" authorityName="Gunther. In" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1372,1780,1805]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Macromotettix</emphasis>
Günther. In
</taxonomicName>
this study, three new species are described as new to science. Thus, to date, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther. In" authorityYear="1939" box="[1220,1384,1816,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1220,1384,1816,1841]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Macromotettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently includes twenty-seven species worldwide, distributed mainly in 
<collectingCountry box="[939,1009,1851,1877]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1116,1851,1877]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1127,1239,1851,1877]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1249,1436,1851,1877]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
and Samoan Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[390,626,1887,1914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" refId="ref12112" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2020) Orthoptera Species File Online. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // Orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org. (Accessed 8 May 2020)." type="url" year="2020">
Cigliano 
<emphasis box="[495,544,1887,1913]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">et al</emphasis>
., 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
